### Line 1: ਸੋਚੈ ਸੋਚਿ ਨ ਹੋਵਈ ਜੇ ਸੋਚੀ ਲਖ ਵਾਰ ॥

sggs:japji_pauri1_line1 a shabd:Line ;
    shabd:index "1"^^xsd:integer ;
    shabd:belongsTo sggs:japji_pauri1 ;
    shabd:gurmukhi "ਸੋਚੈ ਸੋਚਿ ਨ ਹੋਵਈ ਜੇ ਸੋਚੀ ਲਖ ਵਾਰ ॥"@pa ;
    shabd:transliteration "Socẖai socẖ na hovee je socẖī lakh vār."@en-Latn ;
    shabd:translationEn "By thinking and thinking, one does not become pure, even if one thinks hundreds of thousands of times."@en ;
    shabd:hasTheme shabd:EgoEffort,
                   shabd:Intellect,
                   shabd:SpiritualMethodFailure ;
    shabd:commentaryKeypoint "Mere mental effort, analysis, or contemplation alone cannot realize Truth or purify the self, no matter how intensely it is repeated."@en .

### Line 2: ਚੁਪੈ ਚੁਪ ਨ ਹੋਵਈ ਜੇ ਲਾਇ ਰਹਾ ਲਿਵ ਤਾਰ ॥

sggs:japji_pauri1_line2 a shabd:Line ;
    shabd:index "2"^^xsd:integer ;
    shabd:belongsTo sggs:japji_pauri1 ;
    shabd:gurmukhi "ਚੁਪੈ ਚੁਪ ਨ ਹੋਵਈ ਜੇ ਲਾਇ ਰਹਾ ਲਿਵ ਤਾਰ ॥"@pa ;
    shabd:transliteration "Cupai cup na hovee je lāe rahā liv tār."@en-Latn ;
    shabd:translationEn "By remaining silent, silence is not obtained, even if one remains absorbed in deep inward focus."@en ;
    shabd:hasTheme shabd:SpiritualMethodFailure,
                   shabd:EgoEffort ;
    shabd:commentaryKeypoint "External or self-willed silence is not the same as true inner stillness; forced practices without alignment to Hukam cannot yield real peace."@en .

### Line 3: ਭੁਖਿਆ ਭੁਖ ਨ ਉਤਰੀ ਜੇ ਬੰਨਾ ਪੁਰੀਆ ਭਾਰ ॥

sggs:japji_pauri1_line3 a shabd:Line ;
    shabd:index "3"^^xsd:integer ;
    shabd:belongsTo sggs:japji_pauri1 ;
    shabd:gurmukhi "ਭੁਖਿਆ ਭੁਖ ਨ ਉਤਰੀ ਜੇ ਬੰਨਾ ਪੁਰੀਆ ਭਾਰ ॥"@pa ;
    shabd:transliteration "Bhukẖiā bhukẖ na utrī je bannā purīā bhār."@en-Latn ;
    shabd:translationEn "The hunger of the hungry is not appeased, even if they amass loads and loads of worldly goods."@en ;
    shabd:hasTheme shabd:Desire,
                   shabd:EgoEffort,
                   shabd:SpiritualMethodFailure ;
    shabd:commentaryKeypoint "Accumulation of material wealth or experiences cannot satisfy the deeper existential hunger of the soul; craving only multiplies through indulgence."@en .

### Line 4: ਸਹਸ ਸਿਆਣਪਾ ਲਖ ਹੋਹਿ ਤ ਇਕ ਨ ਚਲੈ ਨਾਲਿ ॥

sggs:japji_pauri1_line4 a shabd:Line ;
    shabd:index "4"^^xsd:integer ;
    shabd:belongsTo sggs:japji_pauri1 ;
    shabd:gurmukhi "ਸਹਸ ਸਿਆਣਪਾ ਲਖ ਹੋਹਿ ਤ ਇਕ ਨ ਚਲੈ ਨਾਲਿ ॥"@pa ;
    shabd:transliteration "Sahas siaṇapā lakh hoveh, ta ik na cẖalai nāl."@en-Latn ;
    shabd:translationEn "One may possess hundreds of thousands of clever ideas, yet not even one of them will go along in the end."@en ;
    shabd:hasTheme shabd:Intellect,
                   shabd:EgoEffort ;
    shabd:commentaryKeypoint "No amount of cleverness or intellectual strategy survives death or leads to Truth by itself; intellect without surrender remains barren spiritually."@en .

### Line 5: ਕਿਵ ਸਚਿਆਰਾ ਹੋਈਐ ਕਿਵ ਕੂੜੈ ਤੁਟੈ ਪਾਲਿ ॥

sggs:japji_pauri1_line5 a shabd:Line ;
    shabd:index "5"^^xsd:integer ;
    shabd:belongsTo sggs:japji_pauri1 ;
    shabd:gurmukhi "ਕਿਵ ਸਚਿਆਰਾ ਹੋਈਐ ਕਿਵ ਕੂੜੈ ਤੁਟੈ ਪਾਲਿ ॥"@pa ;
    shabd:transliteration "Kiv sacẖiārā hoeeai, kiv Kūṛai ṭutai pāl."@en-Latn ;
    shabd:translationEn "So then, how can one become truthful? How can the wall of falsehood be torn down?"@en ;
    shabd:hasTheme shabd:Truth,
                   shabd:SpiritualMethodFailure ;
    shabd:commentaryKeypoint "After negating ineffective approaches, Guru Nanak poses the central question: by what means does one align with Truth and break the veil of falsehood?"@en .

### Line 6: ਹੁਕਮਿ ਰਜਾਈ ਚਲਣਾ ਨਾਨਕ ਲਿਖਿਆ ਨਾਲਿ ॥੧॥

sggs:japji_pauri1_line6 a shabd:Line ;
    shabd:index "6"^^xsd:integer ;
    shabd:belongsTo sggs:japji_pauri1 ;
    shabd:gurmukhi "ਹੁਕਮਿ ਰਜਾਈ ਚਲਣਾ ਨਾਨਕ ਲਿਖਿਆ ਨਾਲਿ ॥੧॥"@pa ;
    shabd:transliteration "Hukam rajāī cẖalṇā Nānak likẖiā nāl. ||1||"@en-Latn ;
    shabd:translationEn "O Nanak, one becomes truthful by walking in accordance with Hukam, the Divine Will, which is inscribed together with all beings."@en ;
    shabd:hasTheme shabd:Hukam,
                   shabd:DivineWill,
                   shabd:Truth ;
    shabd:commentaryKeypoint "The answer: live in harmony with Hukam—Divine Order/Will—rather than ego. Truthful living is surrender to what the Divine has inscribed into existence, not self-invented paths."@en .
